\begin_layout Subsubsection
HTTP flow
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When a client wants to communicate with the server, directly or using an
 intermediate proxy, it has to follow the next steps:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Open a TCP conection: It will be used to make a single or multiple request,
 and the response will be received.
 The client can open a new connection, reuse an existing one or open several
 at the same time.
\end_layout

